            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Set it up once and forget it. Every virtual appointment gets a
              Zoom link automatically without any manual intervention needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Seamless Video Conferencing Integration
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Video conferencing integration with Zoom makes virtual meetings
            effortless. Connect your Zoom account to CalendHub once, and every
            virtual appointment automatically gets a unique meeting link
            generated. No more manually creating Zoom meetings, copying links
            into calendar invites, or sending links separately to attendees. The
            entire process happens automatically when appointments are booked.
          </p>

          <p>
            When someone books a virtual appointment through your CalendHub
            scheduling page, the system creates a Zoom meeting instantly and
            includes the link in the booking confirmation. The Zoom link also
            appears in the calendar invite sent to attendees, so they have
            everything they need to join the meeting. Reminder emails include
            the Zoom link again before the meeting, ensuring attendees can
            always find it easily.
          </p>

          <p>
            Each appointment receives its own unique Zoom meeting link. This
            prevents confusion about which link goes with which meeting and
            provides clean separation between different appointments. After the
            meeting ends, that unique link is associated only with that specific
            appointment in your records. This organization makes it easy to
            track which meetings happened and reference past video calls.
          </p>

          <p>
            The integration works seamlessly in the background. You set up your
            Zoom connection in CalendHub settings once, then every virtual
            appointment handles video conferencing automatically. Mark an
            appointment type as virtual, and CalendHub knows to generate Zoom
            links for those bookings. In-person appointment types don't get
            video links - the system only adds them where appropriate. This
            intelligent handling keeps your scheduling clean and professional.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
